The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 ICICI Prudential Life has launched a standalone health insurance plan called Crisis Cover. The plan offers cover against 35 critical illnesses, total and permanent disability and death. The 35 conditions covered include angioplasty, brain surgery, coronary artery bypass surgery, kidney failure, heart attack, major organ transplant, stroke, loss of senses such as hearing, sight and loss of limbs. The scheme comes with a policy term ranging between 10 and 50 years. The maximum age at entry is 60. The sum assured can be between Rs 3 lakh and Rs 20 lakh. 

 Deutsche Asset Management (India) Pvt Ltd, investment manager of Deutsche Mutual Fund, has launched DWS Global Thematic Offshore Fund. It is an open-ended overseas fund-of-funds scheme which will invest predominantly in the Singapore-based DWS Strategic Global Themes Fund. The fund will close on August 28. Minimum investment is Rs 5,000. 

 Escorts Mutual Fund has launched a five-year close-ended fund called Escorts Infrastructure Fund. It will automatically get converted into an open-ended one five years from the date of allotment. It will invest in equity and equity-related instruments of infrastructure firms. The fund closes on August 24.




